The paper deals with the design of mechanisms for facilitating trade between agents, which is a central topic in game theory and mechanism design. The paper also discusses the gain from trade achievable by fixed price mechanisms, which is a topic in economics and optimization. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.EC (Economics and Computation), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
